          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "9 thick targets were produced from natural selenium on",
                "aluminum backings. The backings had a diameter of 35",
                "mm and a thickness of 1.5 mm. The backings featured a",
                "central recess with diameter of 10 mm and depth of",
                "0.5 mm, in which the Se powder was deposited. The",
                "targets then were heated until the Se melted."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " HPGe detector at PTB, used for spectroscopic",
                "analysis of the reaction products"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " low energy photon spectrometer at Goethe",
                "University of Frankfurt, used to determine the",
                "activity of 85Kr"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA",
                "ACTIV",
                "BCINT",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam was wobbled",
                "over the target surface, producing a beam spot of 10",
                "mm diameter. The beam amounted 500 nA, at which the",
                "targets proved to be stable. The typical irradiation",
                "time was 0.6-6.8 h, followed by 10-45 min cooling",
                "time. The measurement time was 2.5-11 h."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " total statistical uncertainty of the data"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " total systematic uncertainty of the data",
                "The values were obtained by propagating the",
                "corresponding uncertainty of charge integration, gamma",
                "branching ratios, number of target atoms, number of",
                "projectiles, and the time measurement. Individual",
                "contributions are not provided.",
                "For the cross section calculation, an uncertainty of",
                "5 % for the path length was assumed. In case of the",
                "Kr-85m yield, an additional asymmetric uncertainty of",
                "10 % was introduced to account for the contribution of",
                "the (a,p) reaction at 15.1 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Experimental cross section were compared with",
                "theoretical values from NON-SMOKER and TALYS-1.6."
              ]
            }
          ],
